# Environment Variables

Add these to your `.env.local` file for local development:

```env
# API Configuration (if needed)
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Three.js Settings
NEXT_PUBLIC_ENABLE_WEBGL=true
```

## Local Development

For development, create a `.env.local` file in the root directory with any necessary variables.

## Production

For production, set these variables in your deployment platform (Vercel, etc.):
- All `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` variables are exposed to the browser
- Keep sensitive data in server-only environment variables
